name: Tethba

attributes.attribute: gave her secret name to the lands she most loved
now parts of Co. Westmeath in the Irish midlands

sources: Monaghan, Patricia. The Encyclopedia of Celtic Mythology and Folklore. Checkmark Books, 2008.
text: A goddess or heroine named Tethba is mentioned in Irish lore. Despite being lesser known, it is said that Tethba imparted her secret name upon the lands she held dearest, now located in Co. Westmeath in the Irish midlands. Such tales are commonly told of the Sovereignty goddess, who is revered as the patron of the land and the king's partner.
